Student Screen Time Analysis (Day 2)

This project analyzes the relationship between students' screen time and their academic performance (test scores).
The goal is to identify patterns and understand how screen time affects learning outcomes.

Objectives
Clean and preprocess raw data
Analyze screen time vs test scores
Identify trends and patterns
Create visualizations for better understanding

Dataset Description
The dataset contains the following columns:

Student ID – Unique identifier
Screen Time (hours) – Daily screen usage
Test Score – Academic performance

Data Cleaning Steps
Handled missing values
Checked for duplicate records
Converted data types where required
Removed inconsistent values

Calculated average test scores
Grouped students based on screen time
Compared performance across categories

